Module scenebuilder.core
Package com.oracle.javafx.scenebuilder.core.ui

Class AbstractPanelController

java.lang.Object
com.oracle.javafx.scenebuilder.core.ui.AbstractPanelController
Direct Known Subclasses:
AbstractFxmlController, AbstractFxmlPanelController
public abstract class AbstractPanelController
extends Object
AbstractPanelController is the abstract base class for all the panel controllers of Scene Builder Kit.

At instantiation time, each panel controller is passed a reference to its editor controller which is hold in editorController.

Subclasses must provide three methods:

  • Spring will create the FX components which compose the panel and provide it using FxmlController.setRoot(Parent) called by SceneBuilderBeanFactory.SceneBuilderBeanFactoryPostProcessor.postProcessBeanFactory(org.springframework.beans.factory.config.ConfigurableListableBeanFactory)
  • fxomDocumentDidChange must keep the panel up to date after the editor controller has changed the base document
  • editorSelectionDidChange must keep the panel up to date after the editor controller has changed the selected objects.
